<chapter id="developers">
<title>Developer's Guide to &mathematik;</title>

<!-- (OPTIONAL) A Programming/Scripting reference chapter should be
used for apps that use plugins or that provide their own scripting hooks
and/or development libraries. -->

<para>
&mathematik; is easily extendable by plugins. You can write
<variablelist>
  <varlistentry>
    <term>Backends:</term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
	A new backend enables you to use the &mathematik; interface with a different program
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
    <term>Assistants:</term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
	Assistants are dialogs, that automate common jobs (like entering a matrix, running a script), offering a nice GUI.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</para>
<para>
Currently there are no special developer tutorials or Api-Docs, so if you want to write a plugin, you'll have to read through the sources.
All interface definitions are in the lib directory. For example implementations, just see some of the plugins shipped with &mathematik;
</para>

</chapter>

